    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Herbert F. Taggart was born in Elk Point, South Dakota. He received his B.A., M.B.A., and Ph.D. from the University of Michigan, and joined the faculty of the School of Business Administration in 1920. Dr. Taggart was Chief of the Cost Accounting Unit of the Research and Planning Division of the National Recovery Administration from 1933 to 1935, and in later years served as a consultant to various government agencies.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The papers, 1934-1980, of Herbert F. Taggart have been arranged in alphabetical order by series name. These are Federal Trade Commission, Governor's Commission on Prepaid Hospital and Medical Care Plans; Journal Articles, and Miscellaneous.</p>
    </scopecontent>
